{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> φορβ-ειά</b>, ἡ, <br /> (φέρβω), written <b>φορβεά</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PCair.Zen.” 781.16 (3rd c.BC), 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus “de fasciis - Opera Hippocratis et Galeni” 14, +others\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; <b>φορβέα</b> codex [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]; also <b>φορβαία</b> (which see):— <b>halter by which a horse is tied to the manger,</b> τῆς ἐπιφατνιδίας φ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Equitandi ratione” 5.1; περιεζῶσθαι τὴν φ. 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1324b16; οἱ ἵπποι ἀπὸ φορβειᾶς ἄγονται 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 15.1.52 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐκ φ. ἕλκειν [ὄνον] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Asin.” 51. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>mouthband</b> of leather <b>put like a halter</b> round the lips of fifers or pipers, to assist them in regulating the sound, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 582 (_anapaest meter_), 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.456b: hence φυσᾷ.. φορβειᾶς ἄτερ\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] blows the pipes without this check, i. e. too loud, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 768. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> a <b>bandage,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Heliodorus Medicus cited in 4th c.AD: Oribasius Medicus 48.39 at Title Page, Sor.[same place], 7th c.AD: Paulus Aegineta Medicus 6.92. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9657","accentedUnicode":"φορβεά","shortDef":"a halter","mediumDef":"a halter","stepGloss":"a halter","stepTransliteration":"forbea","_step_Type":"word","_stepDetailLexicalTag":"[[\"meaning\",\"G9657\",\"a halter\",0,\"φορβεά\"],[\"spelled\",\"G21320\",\"carry-chair\",0,\"φορβαία\"]]"}]}